--- !u!114 &143654200
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 143654198}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e939807b669dc4e7f8275d4d57f9837f, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPC
  npcName: Stephanos
  relationshipGain: 5
  dialogueLow: Oh do not give me that look. I only repeat what I hear. It is hardly
    my fault what people say.
  dialogueNeutral: Neighbour! You will never guess what I saw this morning. Actually
    you might. It involves Kallias and a very large amphora.
  dialogueFriendly: "Between you and me \u2014 and I say this as a friend \u2014
    Nikias has been asking about you. Casually. Very casually. But still."
  dialogueClose: 'I saw Lydia watching you from across the Agora yesterday. She did
    not think anyone noticed. I notice everything. '
  dialogueFestivalGeneric: Festival days are my favourite. Everyone is out, everyone
    is talking. I hear everything.
  dialogueCityDionysia: I heard Kallias arguing with his wife outside the theatre.
    Loudly. During the performance.
  dialogueThargelia: 
  dialoguePanathenaia: Nikias donated a new lamp to the Acropolis. Very generous.
    Very visible. Very Nikias.
  dialogueHephaestia: 
  dialogueThesmophoria: 
  dialoguePyanopsia: 
  dialogueLenaia: Miriam and Theron were seen talking for quite a long time near
    the theatre entrance. Just saying.
  dialogueHaloa: The things people say at a midwinter feast. I could not possibly
    repeat them. But I will.
  interactionRadius: 0.5
  timeCostMinutes: 30
  conversationCooldownSeconds: 10
  promptUI: {fileID: 1065303244}
  romancePromptUI: {fileID: 0}
