--- !u!114 &829595489
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 829595487}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e939807b669dc4e7f8275d4d57f9837f, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPC
  npcName: Lydia
  relationshipGain: 5
  dialogueLow: Please, I have nothing to say to you.
  dialogueNeutral: Good day. My father speaks well of men who apply themselves to
    their work.
  dialogueFriendly: You always seem to find me in the Agora. I confess I have stopped
    minding.
  dialogueClose: I told my father I met you again today. He said nothing. But he
    smiled.
  dialogueFestivalGeneric: I love the city on festival days. Everyone seems kinder
    somehow.
  dialogueCityDionysia: The theatre today was extraordinary. I wept twice and I am
    not ashamed to admit it.
  dialogueThargelia: 
  dialoguePanathenaia: 
  dialogueHephaestia: 
  dialogueThesmophoria: "This festival is not for men's eyes, but I will say \u2014
    it means more to me than I can explain."
  dialoguePyanopsia: 
  dialogueLenaia: 
  dialogueHaloa: There is something freeing about a midwinter feast. The usual rules
    seem far away tonight.
  interactionRadius: 0.5
  timeCostMinutes: 30
  conversationCooldownSeconds: 10
  promptUI: {fileID: 1781816549}
  romancePromptUI: {fileID: 876871423}
