--- !u!114 &878020236
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 878020234}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e939807b669dc4e7f8275d4d57f9837f, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPC
  npcName: Miriam
  relationshipGain: 5
  dialogueLow: "In Alexandria we have a saying \u2014 a closed hand receives nothing.
    You would do well to remember it."
  dialogueNeutral: I have traded in six cities. Athens is the most interesting and
    the most exhausting. Sometimes on the same afternoon.
  dialogueFriendly: You are one of the few here who does not look at me like I arrived
    on the wrong ship. I appreciate that more than you know.
  dialogueClose: I have something set aside for you. Came off a ship from Carthage
    last week. I do not show it to everyone.
  dialogueFestivalGeneric: In Alexandria we celebrate differently but the impulse
    is the same. Humans need to mark time together.
  dialogueCityDionysia: 
  dialogueThargelia: 
  dialoguePanathenaia: 
  dialogueHephaestia: A festival for craftsmen and fire. In Egypt we honour similar
    gods. The names change. The devotion does not.
  dialogueThesmophoria: 
  dialoguePyanopsia: 
  dialogueLenaia: Your winter festivals have a warmth I did not expect. The wine
    helps, I think.
  dialogueHaloa: 
  interactionRadius: 0.5
  timeCostMinutes: 30
  conversationCooldownSeconds: 10
  promptUI: {fileID: 1102140391}
  romancePromptUI: {fileID: 0}
