  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1519368279}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e939807b669dc4e7f8275d4d57f9837f, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPC
  npcName: Theron
  relationshipGain: 5
  dialogueLow: Your thinking is muddled. Come back when you have something worth
    saying.
  dialogueNeutral: "Ah, a new face. I am Theron. Tell me \u2014 what do you believe
    justice truly is?"
  dialogueFriendly: You argue well. I don't agree with you, but you make me think.
    That's rare.
  dialogueClose: I used to think I was the sharpest mind in Athens. You're making
    me reconsider.
  dialogueFestivalGeneric: Festivals remind us that philosophy and piety are not
    enemies. Socrates himself loved a good procession.
  dialogueCityDionysia: 
  dialogueThargelia: Apollo's festival is the only day I feel my arguments are truly
    heard. Perhaps the god lends clarity.
  dialoguePanathenaia: 
  dialogueHephaestia: 
  dialogueThesmophoria: 
  dialoguePyanopsia: A harvest festival for Apollo. I find myself more reflective
    in autumn. The arguments come slower but go deeper.
  dialogueLenaia: 
  dialogueHaloa: 
  interactionRadius: 0.5
  timeCostMinutes: 30
  conversationCooldownSeconds: 10
  promptUI: {fileID: 2060358752}
  romancePromptUI: {fileID: 0}
